frEndptRxBytesCirs.description: Frame Relay Endpoint Rx bytes from port in excess of CIR.

frEndptTxFrmsCirs.name: frEndptTxFrmsCirs
frEndptTxFrmsCirs.description: Frame Relay Endpoint Tx frames from port in excess of CIR.

frEndptTxBytesCirs.name: frEndptTxBytesCirs
frEndptTxBytesCirs.description: Frame Relay Endpoint Tx bytes from port in excess of CIR.

frBwClassTable.name: frBwClassTable
frBwClassTable.description: The Frame Relay Bandwidth Class table.

frBwClassEntry.name: frBwClassEntry
frBwClassEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Bandwidth Class table.

frBwClassIndex.name: frBwClassIndex
frBwClassIndex.description: Index into FrBwClassTable. This index identifies the frame relay bandwidth class.

frBwClassMIR.name: frBwClassMIR
frBwClassMIR.description: The minimum transmit bandwidth (MIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for this end-point.

frBwClassCIR.name: frBwClassCIR
frBwClassCIR.description: The value of this object is equal to the committed information rate (CIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for this end-point.

frBwClassVcQSize.name: frBwClassVcQSize
frBwClassVcQSize.description: The value of this object is the maximum queue depth (in bytes) for this end-point.

frBwClassBc.name: frBwClassBc
frBwClassBc.description: The value of this object is equal to the committed burst size (Bc) parameter (in bytes) for this end-point.

frBwClassPIR.name: frBwClassPIR
frBwClassPIR.description: The peak transmit bandwidth (PIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for this end-point.

frBwClassBe.name: frBwClassBe
frBwClassBe.description: The value of this object is equal to the excess burst size (Be) parameter (in bytes) for this end-point.

frBwClassCMAX.name: frBwClassCMAX
frBwClassCMAX.description: The maximum credits that can be accrued for this end-point.

frBwClassEcnQSize.name: frBwClassEcnQSize
frBwClassEcnQSize.description: The threshold setting used by the explicit congestion notification feature for this end-point's transmit queue. This value is specified in bytes.

frBwClassQIR.name: frBwClassQIR
frBwClassQIR.description: The transmit quiescent information rate (QIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for this end-point. This value can range between the MIR and PIR values and must be between 2400 and 2048000. This parameter has meaning only if the frEndptEnableFST parameter is set to true.

frBwClassPercUtil.name: frBwClassPercUtil
frBwClassPercUtil.description: The value of this object is equal to the channel percentage utilization setting for this end-point. This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by this end-point.

frBwClassOeMIR.name: frBwClassOeMIR
frBwClassOeMIR.description: The minimum receive bandwidth (MIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for the other end-point.

frBwClassOeCIR.name: frBwClassOeCIR
frBwClassOeCIR.description: The value of this object is equal to the committed information rate (CIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for the other end-point.

frBwClassOeVcQSize.name: frBwClassOeVcQSize
frBwClassOeVcQSize.description: The value of this object is the maximum queue depth (in bytes) for this end-point.

frBwClassOeBc.name: frBwClassOeBc
frBwClassOeBc.description: The value of this object is equal to the committed burst size (Bc) parameter (in bytes) for the end-point.

frBwClassOePIR.name: frBwClassOePIR
frBwClassOePIR.description: The peak receive bandwidth (PIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for the other end-point.

frBwClassOeBe.name: frBwClassOeBe
frBwClassOeBe.description: The value of this object is equal to the excess burst size (Be) parameter (in bytes) for the other end-point.

frBwClassOeCMAX.name: frBwClassOeCMAX
frBwClassOeCMAX.description: The maximum credits that can be accrued for the other end-point.

frBwClassOeEcnQSize.name: frBwClassOeEcnQSize
frBwClassOeEcnQSize.description: The threshold setting used by the explicit congestion notification feature for the other end-point's receive queue. This value is specified in bytes.

frBwClassOeQIR.name: frBwClassOeQIR
frBwClassOeQIR.description: The receive quiescent information rate (QIR) parameter (in 100s of bits per second) for the other end-point.

frBwClassOePercUtil.name: frBwClassOePercUtil
frBwClassOePercUtil.description: The value of this object is equal to the channel percentage utilization setting for the other end-point.

frBwClassEnableFST.name: frBwClassEnableFST
frBwClassEnableFST.description: The value of this object determines whether or not the ForeSight option is being used for this . If set to false, then ForeSight is not used, and if true then ForeSight will be used.

frBwClassDescription.name: frBwClassDescription
frBwClassDescription.description: This MIB object contains a textual description of this frame relay bandwidth class.

atmEndptTable.name: atmEndptTable
atmEndptTable.description: The ATM End-Point table. This table is used to model a PVC end-point. This table contains the traffic parameters for ATM end-point.

atmEndptEntry.name: atmEndptEntry
atmEndptEntry.description: An entry in the ATM End-point table.

atmEndptIndex.name: atmEndptIndex
atmEndptIndex.description: Index into table for this end-point. Although only 5000 endpoints may exist on a node, 10000 possible index values exist to support DAX (intra-node) connections.

atmEndptDesc.name: atmEndptDesc
atmEndptDesc.description: String describing this end-point. Contains information about the domain, nodename, slot, port, vpi, and vci for the end-point. For example, D1.Node1.12.1.100.200, is a valid description. Domain and nodename need not be given but slot, port, VPI and VCI values must exist; 12.1.100.200 is valid. A virtual path connection endpoint of the form 12.1.100.* is also valid. For a basis port the last 4 bits of the VPI must be between 3 and 14.

atmOtherEndptIndex.name: atmOtherEndptIndex
atmOtherEndptIndex.description: Index into remote node's atmEndptTable for this end-point. For DAX (intra-node) connections, this index is associated with the local node and will be in the range of 5000 to 9999.

atmOtherEndptDesc.name: atmOtherEndptDesc
atmOtherEndptDesc.description: String describing the remote PVC end-point. Contains information about the domain, nodename, slot, port, vpi, and vci for the end-point. For example, D2.Node2.10.1.100.200, is a valid description. Nodename, slot, port, VPI and VCI values must exist. A virtual path connection endpoint of the form D2.Node2.10.1.100.* is also valid. For a basis port the last 4 bits of the VPI must be between 3 and 14.

atmEndptAdminStatus.name: atmEndptAdminStatus
atmEndptAdminStatus.description: User requested state for end-point table row. A user can create this VC or delete this VC by setting this object appropriately. If the end-point is to be modified, set this object identifier to be modify.

atmEndptOperStatus.name: atmEndptOperStatus
atmEndptOperStatus.description: Actual state of the end-point. If the state is failed, then look to the objects atmNoRouteFoundFailure, atmBumpFailure, atmEndPointFailure, and atmTestFailure to determine reason for failure.

atmNoRouteFoundFailure.name: atmNoRouteFoundFailure
atmNoRouteFoundFailure.description: End-point is failed is because no route to the remote end-point could be found.

atmBumpFailure.name: atmBumpFailure
atmBumpFailure.description: End-point is failed because of insufficient bandwidth to route to the remote end-point. This may have also been caused because a higher priority connection took this end-point's bandwidth. A higher priority connection is one with the lowest class of service (COS).

atmEndPointFailure.name: atmEndPointFailure
atmEndPointFailure.description: End-point is failed because of a remote end-point failure. The remote end-point is on a node that resides in another domain making the connection an inter-domain connection.

atmTestFailure.name: atmTestFailure
atmTestFailure.description: End-point is failed because of the failure of a connection test.

atmConnPtr.name: atmConnPtr
atmConnPtr.description: Pointer to general connection information. Using this pointer the user can obtain connection status, and routing information. Specifically, this is an object identifier specifying the first column of the appropriate row in the connTable.

atmNextPtr.name: atmNextPtr
atmNextPtr.description: Pointer to next end-point information. This allows logical sets of end-points to be linked up. For example, the end-points associated with a bundle or group. Specifically, this is an object identifier specifying the first column of the appropriate row in the atmEndptTable.

atmNextOnPortPtr.name: atmNextOnPortPtr
atmNextOnPortPtr.description: Pointer to next end-point information for the port associated with this end-point. For example, using this pointer all atm end-points on a given slot.port can be determined. Specifically, this is an object identifier specifying the first column of the appropriate row in the atmEndptTable.

atmEndptConnDesc.name: atmEndptConnDesc
atmEndptConnDesc.description: A string that has been defined for the connection to give a more descriptive name. Connections can be given clear text names in order to make them more human readable.

atmEndptTrkAvoidType.name: atmEndptTrkAvoidType
atmEndptTrkAvoidType.description: User selectable types of trunks to avoid for the transfer of ATM data. Current choices are to avoid satellite links, terrestrial links, or to not avoid any specific type of link. This object is optional during the creation of an endpoint.

atmEndptTrkAvoidZCS.name: atmEndptTrkAvoidZCS
atmEndptTrkAvoidZCS.description: Flag to force the connection to avoid trunks with zero code suppression (ZCS). This object is optional during the creation of an endpoint.

atmEndptSubType.name: atmEndptSubType
atmEndptSubType.description: ATM endpoint subtype object. atf - Interworking conn (without Foresight) vbr - Variable Bit Rate Conn (No ForeSight) cbr - Constant Bit Rate Conn (No ForeSight) abr - Available Bit Rte Conn (With ForeSight) atfst - Interworking Conn (with ForeSight).

atmEndptBWClass.name: atmEndptBWClass
atmEndptBWClass.description: User selectable connection class which defines the operating parameters for the connection. Any or all of these parameters can be overridden by specifying the bandwidth parameters directly. This object is required during the creation of an endpoint.

atmEndptMIR.name: atmEndptMIR
atmEndptMIR.description: The minimum transmit bandwidth (MIR) parameter (in cells per second) for this end-point. The maximum value for this object is the port speed of the associated interface. This object does not apply to CBR connections. For VBR and ATF without Foresight connections this object corresponds to the PCR(0+1) parameter defined by ATM standard documents. For ABR and ATF with Foresight connections this object corresponds to the Minimum Cell Rate (MCR).

atmEndptCIR.name: atmEndptCIR
atmEndptCIR.description: The value of this object is equal to the committed information rate (CIR) parameter (in cells per second) for this end-point. For CBR connections this object corresponds to the PCR(0+1) parameter defined by ATM standard documents. For VBR, ABR, and ATF connections this object corresponds to the Sustainable Cell Rate (SCR) defined by ATM standard documents. The maximum value for this object is the port speed of the associated interface. For T3 and E3 interfaces only multiples of 10 are used internally. For OC3 interfaces only values in the following set are used internally: 11, 17, 23, 34, 45, 68, 90, 136, 181, 271, 362, 543, 723, 1085, 1447, 2170, 2894, 4340, 5787, 8681, 11574, 17361, 23148, 34722, 46296, 69444, 92593, 138889, 185185, 277778. Values between 277778 and 353208 are all valid for OC3 interfaces. All values in the valid range for a given interface will be accepted, but they will be internally rounded up to the closest higher value valid for that interface.

atmEndptVcQSize.name: atmEndptVcQSize
atmEndptVcQSize.description: The value of this object is the maximum queue depth (in cells) for this end-point. This object does not apply to vbr or cbr connections.

atmEndptPIR.name: atmEndptPIR
atmEndptPIR.description: The peak transmit bandwidth (PIR) parameter (in cells per second) for this end-point. The maximum value for this object is the port speed of the associated interface. This object applies only to ABR and ATF with Foresight connections and corresponds to the PCR(0+1) parameter defined by ATM standard documents.

atmEndptEfciQSize.name: atmEndptEfciQSize
atmEndptEfciQSize.description: The threshold setting used by the explicit congestion notification feature for this end-point's transmit queue. This value is a percentage. This object does not apply to vbr or cbr connections.

atmEndptQIR.name: atmEndptQIR
atmEndptQIR.description: The transmit quiescent information rate (QIR) parameter (in cells per second) for this end-point. This value can range between the MIR and PIR values and must be between 0 and 96000. This parameter has meaning only for Foresight connections. This object corresponds to the Initial Cell Rate (ICR).

atmEndptPercUtil.name: atmEndptPercUtil
atmEndptPercUtil.description: The value of this object is equal to the channel percentage utilization setting for this end-point. This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by this end-point.

atmEndptCBS.name: atmEndptCBS
atmEndptCBS.description: The value of this object is equal to the Compliant Burst Size in cells for this end-point. The maximum value for this object on OC3 end points is 1000. This object corresponds to the Maximum Burst Size (MBS) defined by ATM standard documents. This object can be set if atmEndptUPC is enabled.

atmEndptIBS.name: atmEndptIBS
atmEndptIBS.description: The value of this object is equal to the Initial Burst Size in cells for this end-point. The maximum value for this object on OC3 end points is 1000. This object does not apply to vbr or cbr connections.

atmEndptMFS.name: atmEndptMFS

atmEndptLoCLP.name: atmEndptLoCLP

atmEndptCLPTagging.name: atmEndptCLPTagging

atmEndptUPC.name: atmEndptUPC
atmEndptUPC.description: The value of this object enables the UPC algorithm.

atmEndptEnableFST.name: atmEndptEnableFST
atmEndptEnableFST.description: The value of this object determines whether or not the ForeSight option is being used for this . If set to false, then ForeSight is not used, and if true then ForeSight will be used. Foresight option is not supported on OC3 interfaces.

atmEndptRateUpICA.name: atmEndptRateUpICA
atmEndptRateUpICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Rate Up value in cells per second per adjust for this end point.

atmEndptRateDnICA.name: atmEndptRateDnICA
atmEndptRateDnICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Rate Down value expressed as percentage of MCR.

atmEndptFastDnICA.name: atmEndptFastDnICA
atmEndptFastDnICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Fast Down value expressed as percentage of MCR.

atmEndptToQIR.name: atmEndptToQIR
atmEndptToQIR.description: The value of this object is equal to the QIR timeout value. This object corresponds to the Initial Cell Rate (ICR) timeout.

atmEndptMinAdjustICA.name: atmEndptMinAdjustICA
atmEndptMinAdjustICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight minimum adjustment period.

atmEndptGroupFlag.name: atmEndptGroupFlag
atmEndptGroupFlag.description: Specifies whether this is a grouped connection. Note that MIB object connGroupFlag provides grouping information about all the connections using that connTable entry whereas this object provides same information for this end point.

atmEndptOamStatus.name: atmEndptOamStatus
atmEndptOamStatus.description: The end to end OAM state.

atmEndptBCM.name: atmEndptBCM
atmEndptBCM.description: The value of this object enables the generation of RM cells when congestion is detected in this connection.

atmEndptFGCRA.name: atmEndptFGCRA
atmEndptFGCRA.description: The value of this object enables FGCRA. FGCRA (Frame-based Generic Rate Control Algorithm) is applicable with AAL-5 traffic only. This object can be set if atmEndptUPC is enabled.

atmEndptLocLpbkState.name: atmEndptLocLpbkState
atmEndptLocLpbkState.description: Specifies the Local Loopback State the user would like to set for the endpoint.

atmEndptLpbkStatus.name: atmEndptLpbkStatus

There currently are 16 loopback states an endpoint may have configured. The bitmap is defined as follows from LSB to MSB: Remote nodes remote muxbus loopback Remote nodes tstcon loopback Local nodes remoet muxbus loopback Local nodes tstcon loopback Local nodes local muxbus loopback Local nodes port loopback Local nodes port test loopback Remote nodes local muxbus loopback Remote nodes port loopback Remote nodes port test looback Local DDS network requested CSU loopback Remote DDS network requested CSU loopback Local DDS network requested DSU loopback Remote DDS network requested DSU loopback Local DDS external loopback Remote DDS external loopback

atmEndptTestType.name: atmEndptTestType

TestDelay calculates the delay incurred on the connection. The result of the TestDelay may then be accessed through the atmEndptRtdTestDelay object. This is a non-disruptive test.

atmEndptRtdTestDelay.name: atmEndptRtdTestDelay
atmEndptRtdTestDelay.description: The value of this object is the calculated round trip delay (measured in milliseconds) for an OAM cell that is sent across the network to the remote node where it is looped back and returned to this node. A delay test is invoked through setting the the atmEndptTestType object to TestDelay.

atmEndptOeBCM.name: atmEndptOeBCM
atmEndptOeBCM.description: The value of this object enables the generation of RM cells when congestion is detected in this connection. This is the other endpoint view.

atmEndptOeFGCRA.name: atmEndptOeFGCRA
atmEndptOeFGCRA.description: The value of this object enables FGCRA. FGCRA (Frame-based Generic Rate Control Algorithm) is applicable with AAL-5 traffic only. This object can be set if atmEndptUPC is enabled. This is the other endpoint view.

atmEndptGroupDesc.name: atmEndptGroupDesc
atmEndptGroupDesc.description: String describing the group this endpoint is associated with. The format of the group text description is domain.node.grp-number (Example, D2.node1.1).

atmEndptLocRmtLpbkState.name: atmEndptLocRmtLpbkState
atmEndptLocRmtLpbkState.description: Specifies the Local-Remote Loopback State the user would like to set for the endpoint.

atmEndptScrPlc.name: atmEndptScrPlc
atmEndptScrPlc.description: Specifies the traffic policing for this end point This object can be set only if atmEndptUPC is enabled.

atmEndptOeScrPlc.name: atmEndptOeScrPlc
atmEndptOeScrPlc.description: Specifies the traffic policing for the other end point. This object can be set only if atmEndptUPC is enabled.

atmEndptPCR0.name: atmEndptPCR0
atmEndptPCR0.description: The peak cell rate (in cells per second) for the second bucket for this end point. This object corresponds to the parameter PCR(0) in standard ATM documents and applies only to CBR connections. This object can be set only if atmEndptUPC is enabled. PCR(0) must be less or equal than PCR(0+1).

atmEndptOePCR0.name: atmEndptOePCR0

PCR(0) must be less or equal than PCR(0+1).

atmEndptCDVT0.name: atmEndptCDVT0

atmEndptOeCDVT0.name: atmEndptOeCDVT0

atmEndptOeRateUpICA.name: atmEndptOeRateUpICA

atmEndptFRTT.name: atmEndptFRTT
atmEndptFRTT.description: The Fixed Round-Trip Time (FRTT) is the sum of the fixed and propagation delays from the source to a destination and back. . Units: milliseconds. . Applicable connection types: standard ABR only . Default: 0 . Dependency: VSVD = enable(1)

atmEndptTBE.name: atmEndptTBE
atmEndptTBE.description: Transient Buffer Exposure (TBE) is the negotiated number of cells that the network would like to limit the source to sending during startup periods, before the first RM-cell returns. . Units: cells . Applicable connection types: standard ABR only . Default: 1048320 . Dependency: VSVD = enable(1)

atmEndptVSVD.name: atmEndptVSVD
atmEndptVSVD.description: Virtual Source/Virtual Destination (VS/VD) is used to divide an ABR connection into two or more separately controlled ABR segment. This flag indicates whether the ATM end points (both ends) will serve as VS/VD or not. . Applicable connection types: . standard ABR . ABRFST: Cannot be set, but always enable(1). . ATFST : Cannot be set, but always enable(1). . Dependency: . The object CANNOT be MODIFIED after the first set! All Subsequent sets will be rejected! The object can be set when only add ABRSTD connection. ============================================ ABRSTD VSVD option ABRSTD ABRFST ATFST ============================================= available Both (Yes) (Yes) unavalable No (Yes) (Yes) Note: . Yes = Has to be set to enable(1) No = Has to be set to disable(2) Both = can be set to either enable(1) or disable(2) (Yes) = Always enabled and cannot be set. (No) = Always disabled and cannot be set. . Default: disable(2)

atmEndptPolicing.name: atmEndptPolicing
atmEndptPolicing.description: Specifies the traffic policing for this end point. --------------- ---------- ---------- Policing Type 1st Bucket 2nd Bucket --------------- ---------- ---------- vbr.1 CLP(0+1) CLP(0+1) vbr.2 CLP(0+1) CLP(0) vbr.3 CLP(0+1) CLP(0) with CLP Tagging pcrplc CLP(0+1) none none none none . Applicable connection types: . CBR (only pcrplc(4) or none(5)), VBR, ATFR, . standard ABR, ABR FST, ATFST: VSVD = enable(1) . Default: vbr3(3) . Dependency: Not allowed for standard ABR without VSVD. In this case, it is set to pcrplc(4).

atmEndptPCR.name: atmEndptPCR
atmEndptPCR.description: PCR(0+1), Peak Cell Rate, specifies an upper bound on rate at which traffic can be submitted on an ATM connection. This object applies to the First Leaky Bucket for leaving cells with Cell Loss Priority of 0 or 1. . Units: cells per second. . Applicable connection types: UBR, CBR, VBR, ATFR, standard ABR, ABR FST, ATFST . Default: 50 or MCR . Ranges: T3 : MCR-96000 E3 : MCR-80000 OC3 : MCR-353208 OC12: MCR-1412832

atmBwClassEnableFST.name: atmBwClassEnableFST
atmBwClassEnableFST.description: The value of this object determines whether or not the ForeSight option is being used for this . If set to false, then ForeSight is not used, and if true then ForeSight will be used.

atmBwClassRateUpICA.name: atmBwClassRateUpICA
atmBwClassRateUpICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Rate Up value in cells per second per adjust for this end point.

atmBwClassRateDnICA.name: atmBwClassRateDnICA
atmBwClassRateDnICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Rate Down value expressed as percentage of MCR.

atmBwClassFastDnICA.name: atmBwClassFastDnICA
atmBwClassFastDnICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Fast Down value expressed as percentage of MCR.

atmBwClassToQIR.name: atmBwClassToQIR
atmBwClassToQIR.description: The value of this object is equal to the QIR timeout value. This object corresponds to the Initial Cell Rate (ICR) timeout.

atmBwClassMinAdjustICA.name: atmBwClassMinAdjustICA
atmBwClassMinAdjustICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight minimum adjustment period.

atmBwClassDescription.name: atmBwClassDescription
atmBwClassDescription.description: This MIB object contains a textual description of this frame relay bandwidth class.

atmBwClassBCM.name: atmBwClassBCM
atmBwClassBCM.description: The value of this object enables the generation of RM cells when congestion is detected in the connection.

atmBwClassFGCRA.name: atmBwClassFGCRA
atmBwClassFGCRA.description: The value of this object enables FGCRA. FGCRA (Frame-based Generic Rate Control Algorithm) is applicable with AAL-5 traffic only.

atmBwClassOeBCM.name: atmBwClassOeBCM
atmBwClassOeBCM.description: The value of this object enables the generation of RM cells when congestion is detected in the connection. This is the other endpoint view.

atmBwClassOeFGCRA.name: atmBwClassOeFGCRA
atmBwClassOeFGCRA.description: The value of this object enables FGCRA. FGCRA (Frame-based Generic Rate Control Algorithm) is applicable with AAL-5 traffic only. This is the other endpoint view.

atmBwClassConType.name: atmBwClassConType
atmBwClassConType.description: The value of this object defines the connection type associated with this class.

atmBwClassScrPlc.name: atmBwClassScrPlc
atmBwClassScrPlc.description: Specifies the traffic policing for this end point.

atmBwClassOeScrPlc.name: atmBwClassOeScrPlc
atmBwClassOeScrPlc.description: Specifies the traffic policing for the other end point.

atmBwClassPCR0.name: atmBwClassPCR0
atmBwClassPCR0.description: The peak cell rate (in cells per second) for the second bucket for this end point. This object corresponds to the parameter PCR(0) in standard ATM documents.

atmBwClassOePCR0.name: atmBwClassOePCR0
atmBwClassOePCR0.description: The peak cell rate (in cells per second) for the second bucket for the other end point. This object corresponds to the parameter PCR(0) in standard ATM documents.

atmBwClassCDVT0.name: atmBwClassCDVT0
atmBwClassCDVT0.description: The cell delay variation tolerance for the second bucket for this end point. This object corresponds to the parameter CDVT(0) in standard ATM documents.

atmBwClassOeCDVT0.name: atmBwClassOeCDVT0
atmBwClassOeCDVT0.description: The cell delay variation tolerance for the second bucket for the other end point. This object corresponds to the parameter CDVT(0) in standard ATM documents.

atmBwClassOeRateUpICA.name: atmBwClassOeRateUpICA
atmBwClassOeRateUpICA.description: The value of this object is equal to the ForeSight Rate Up value in cells per second per adjust for the other end point.

atmEndptMapSlot.description: This MIB object contains the slot number associated with the requested connection endpoint.

atmEndptMapPort.name: atmEndptMapPort

atmEndptMapVpi.description: This MIB object contains the ATM endpoint VPI associated with the requested connection endpoint.

atmEndptStatEntry.description: An entry in the ATM End-point Statistics table.

atmCellsTxNets.description: The number of received cells delivered to the network.

atmClpRxs.name: atmClpRxs

atmViolRxs.name: atmViolRxs
atmViolRxs.description: The number of cells that violated UPC.

atmDiscardVcqClpThs.name: atmDiscardVcqClpThs
atmDiscardVcqClpThs.description: The number of cells with CLP set that were discarded due to VC queue exceeding CLP thresholds.

atmDiscardVcqFulls.name: atmDiscardVcqFulls
atmDiscardVcqFulls.description: The number of received cells that were discarded due to the VC queue being full.

atmEfciRxs.name: atmEfciRxs
atmEfciRxs.description: The number of cells received with EFCI set.

atmNonCompRxs.name: atmNonCompRxs
atmNonCompRxs.description: The number of non-compliant cells received.

atmDiscardFails.name: atmDiscardFails
atmDiscardFails.description: The number of received cells discarded due to the connection being in failed state.

atmAvgVcqDepths.name: atmAvgVcqDepths
atmAvgVcqDepths.description: The average queue depth of the VC queue.

atmDiscardRsrcOflows.name: atmDiscardRsrcOflows
atmDiscardRsrcOflows.description: The number of received cells discarded due to a resource overflow (e.g. cell buffer full).

atmDiscardSbinFulls.name: atmDiscardSbinFulls
atmDiscardSbinFulls.description: The number of cells discarded on receipt from from the port due to Sbin full.

atmBcmRxs.name: atmBcmRxs
atmBcmRxs.description: The number of BCM cells received from the port. This object only applies to NNI ports. For UNI ports returns 0.

atmBcmTxs.name: atmBcmTxs
atmBcmTxs.description: The number of BCM cells transmitted to the network. This object only applies to NNI ports. For UNI ports returns 0.

atmOamTxs.name: atmOamTxs
atmOamTxs.description: The number of OAM cells transmitted to the network.

atmDiscardQbinFulls.name: atmDiscardQbinFulls
atmDiscardQbinFulls.description: The number of cells discarded due to the egress Qbin being full.

atmDiscardQbinClpThs.name: atmDiscardQbinClpThs
atmDiscardQbinClpThs.description: The number of cells with CLP set that are discarded due to the egress Qbin exceeding CLP thresholds.

atmCellsRxNets.name: atmCellsRxNets
atmCellsRxNets.description: The number of cells received from the network.

atmClpTxs.name: atmClpTxs
atmClpTxs.description: The number of cells transmitted to the port that had their CLP bit set.

atmEfciTxs.name: atmEfciTxs
atmEfciTxs.description: The number of cells transmitted by the port to the line interface that had EFCI set.

atmCellsTxPorts.name: atmCellsTxPorts
atmCellsTxPorts.description: The number of cells transmitted to the port interface.

atmAisRxs.name: atmAisRxs
atmAisRxs.description: The number of received AIS cells.

atmFerfRxs.name: atmFerfRxs
atmFerfRxs.description: The number of received FERF cells.

voiceEndptTable.name: voiceEndptTable
voiceEndptTable.description: The voice channel connection table has Channel Connection information. This table is used to model a specific Voice Channel connection. This table contains parameters which are requrired to create a Voice conneciton and configure the channel.

voiceEndptEntry.name: voiceEndptEntry
voiceEndptEntry.description: An entry in the voice Endpoint Channel Connection table.

voiceEndptIndex.name: voiceEndptIndex
voiceEndptIndex.description: The index for this Voice Connection. This is the index to this table.

voiceOtherEndptIndex.name: voiceOtherEndptIndex
voiceOtherEndptIndex.description: Index into remote node's voiceEndptTable for this channel end-point. For local (intra-node) connections, this index is associated with the local node and will be in the range of 1024 to 2047.

voiceEndptDesc.name: voiceEndptDesc
voiceEndptDesc.description: String describing this voice Channel. Contains information about the domain, nodename, slot, channel, for the connection. For example, D1.Node1.12.1, is a valid description. Domain and nodename need not be given but slot, channel values must exist; 12.1 is valid. This variable value has to specified for a Creating an voiceEndptEntry.

voiceOtherEndptDesc.name: voiceOtherEndptDesc
voiceOtherEndptDesc.description: String describing the remote channel. Contains information about the domain, nodename, slot, channel, for the connection. For example, D2.Node2.10.5, is a valid description. Nodename, slot, channel values must exist; Node2.10.5 is valid. This variable value has to be specified for creating an voiceEndptEntry.

voiceEndptConnDesc.name: voiceEndptConnDesc
voiceEndptConnDesc.description: A string that has been defined for the connection to give a more descriptive name. Connections can be given clear text names in order to make them more human readable.

voiceEndptAdminStatus.name: voiceEndptAdminStatus
voiceEndptAdminStatus.description: User requested state for voice endpoint table row. A user can create / delete / modify this voice channel connection by setting this object appropriately. The user also has the capability to test a particular object. For this capability, the user must set this value to test. If a Get operation is performed on this variable, -1 shall be returned to the NMS.

voiceEndptOperStatus.name: voiceEndptOperStatus
voiceEndptOperStatus.description: Actual state of the voice channel.If the state is failed, then look to the objects voiceNoRouteFoundFailure, voiceBumpFailure, and voiceTestFailure to determine reason for failure.

voiceEndptRateType.name: voiceEndptRateType
voiceEndptRateType.description: Represents the type of voice connection. Each of them has been described below briefly. Type Description a32 Uses ADPCM only. Can select 32/24/16 Kbps a24 compression. a16 a16z Standard 16Kbps ADPCM only. compressed code can have strings of zeros and should be used on lines that have other zero code supression c32 Uses both ADPCM and Voice Activity detection (VAD). c24 Can select 32/24/16 Kbps ADPCM compression. c16 c16z Standard 16Kbps ADPCM and Voice Activity detection. Similar to 16z. Use on ZCS trunks only. p 64Kbps connection. No compression t Transparent. Clean 64Kbps connection. No Compression. This variable value has to be specified for creating an voiceEndptEntry.

voiceEndPointFailure.name: voiceEndPointFailure
voiceEndPointFailure.description: End-point is failed because of a remote end-point failure. The remote end-point is on a node that resides in another domain making the connection an inter-domain connection.

voiceNoRouteFoundFailure.name: voiceNoRouteFoundFailure
voiceNoRouteFoundFailure.description: Channel connection is failed is because no route to the remote Channel could be found.

voiceBumpFailure.name: voiceBumpFailure
voiceBumpFailure.description: Channel Connection is failed because of insufficient bandwidth to route to the remote Channel. This may have also been caused because a higher priority connection took this channel's bandwidth. A higher priority connection is one with the lowest class of service (COS).

voiceTestFailure.name: voiceTestFailure
voiceTestFailure.description: Channel is failed because of the failure of a connection test.

voiceEndptTestType.name: voiceEndptTestType
voiceEndptTestType.description: Specifies the type of test the user would like to conduct on this endpoint. Only testCon is currently defined. TestCon performs a test of voice path integrity in the connection. Only write is allowed on this object. A -1 is returned to the NMS if a GET is recevied on this object

voiceEndptLpbkStatus.name: voiceEndptLpbkStatus
voiceEndptLpbkStatus.description: Specifies the current Loopback State of the endpoint. The value returned from this object is a bitmap of the current loopback states associated with this end point. The bitmap is defined below: LP-RMT-RMT 0 /* Remote nodes remote muxbus loopback */ LP-RMT-TST 1 /* Remote nodes tstcon loopback */ LP-LOC-RMT 2 /* Local nodes remote muxbus loopback */ LP-LOC-TST 3 /* Local nodes tstcon loopback */ LP-LOC-LOC 4 /* Local nodes local muxbus loopback */ LP-LOC-PORT 5 /* Local nodes port loopback */ LP-LOC-TPORT 6 /* Local nodes port test loopback */ LP-RMT-LOC 7 /* Remote nodes local muxbus loopback */ LP-RMT-PORT 8 /* Remote nodes port loopback */ LP-RMT-TPORT 9 /* Remote nodes port test looback */ LP-LOC-CSU 10 /* Local DDS network requested CSU loopback */ LP-RMT-CSU 11 /* Remote DDS network requested CSU loopback */ LP-LOC-DSU 12 /* Local DDS network requested DSU loopback */ LP-RMT-DSU 13 /* Remote DDS network requested DSU loopback */ LP-LOC-EXT 14 /* Local DDS external loopback */ LP-RMT-EXT 15 /* Remote DDS external loopback */

voiceConnPtr.name: voiceConnPtr
voiceConnPtr.description: Pointer to general connection information. Using this pointer the user can obtain connection status, and routing information. Specifically, this is an object identifier specifying the first column of the appropriate row in the connTable.

voiceChannelPtr.name: voiceChannelPtr
voiceChannelPtr.description: Pointer to channel configuration information. Using this pointer the user can obtain all channel configuration information. Specifically, this is an object identifier specifying the first column of the appropriate row in the voiceChannelTable.

voiceEndptTrkAvoidType.name: voiceEndptTrkAvoidType
voiceEndptTrkAvoidType.description: User selectable types of trunks to avoid for the transfer of voice channel data. Current choices are to avoid satellite links, terrestrial links, or to not avoid any specific type of link. This object is optional during the creation of the endpoint.

voiceEndptAvoidZCS.name: voiceEndptAvoidZCS
voiceEndptAvoidZCS.description: Flag to force the connection to avoid trunks with zero code suppression (ZCS). This object is optional during the creation of the endpoint.

voiceEndptState.name: voiceEndptState
voiceEndptState.description: It gives the state of the connection end point.

voiceEndptAdv.name: voiceEndptAdv
voiceEndptAdv.description: It represents if the endpoint supports Adaptve voice capability.

voiceOtherEndptAdv.name: voiceOtherEndptAdv
voiceOtherEndptAdv.description: It represents if the other endpoint supports Adaptve voice capability.

voiceEndptEncoding.name: voiceEndptEncoding
voiceEndptEncoding.description: It represents the type of Encoding used at this this Endpoint.

voiceOtherEndptEncoding.name: voiceOtherEndptEncoding
voiceOtherEndptEncoding.description: It represents the type of Encoding used at the other Endpoint.

voiceEndptEndptType.name: voiceEndptEndptType
voiceEndptEndptType.description: It represents the end point type

voiceEndptLocLpbkState.name: voiceEndptLocLpbkState
voiceEndptLocLpbkState.description: Specifies the Local Loopback State the user would like to set for the endpoint.

voiceStatEntry.name: voiceStatEntry
voiceStatEntry.description: An entry in the voice channel statistics table.

voiceStatPktsRxs.name: voiceStatPktsRxs
voiceStatPktsRxs.description: The number of packets received from the muxbus by the local port card.

voiceStatPktsXmits.name: voiceStatPktsXmits
voiceStatPktsXmits.description: The number of packets transmitted from the local port card onto the Mux Bus.

voiceStatRxPktsDscds.name: voiceStatRxPktsDscds
voiceStatRxPktsDscds.description: The number of packets received from the muxbus by the local port card which are discarded before being transmitted out to the port.

voiceStatSprvPktsXmits.name: voiceStatSprvPktsXmits
voiceStatSprvPktsXmits.description: The number of supervisory packets transmitted from the local port onto the Muxbus. Supervisory packets reflect signalling bit transitions for voice connections.

voiceStatSprvPktsRcvs.name: voiceStatSprvPktsRcvs
voiceStatSprvPktsRcvs.description: The number of supervisory packets received from Muxbus associated with a connection.

voiceStatV25ModemOns.name: voiceStatV25ModemOns
voiceStatV25ModemOns.description: The number of seconds the V.25 modem is detected and the connection is upgraded to PCM.

voiceStatDsiOns.name: voiceStatDsiOns
voiceStatDsiOns.description: The number of seconds that a connection is performing Digital speech interpolation (DSI).

voiceStatOffhks.name: voiceStatOffhks
voiceStatOffhks.description: The number of seconds that a connection is offhook. The onhook state is determined by onhook A/B/C/D bits defined by variables in the voiceEndpttable. A connection which is not onhook is treated as offhook.

voiceStatInservices.name: voiceStatInservices
voiceStatInservices.description: The number of seconds a connection is inservice. A connection is said to be in-service if its endpoints are not in alarm, the cards required to support this connection are present, and the connection is routed.

voiceEndptMapEntry.name: voiceEndptMapEntry
voiceEndptMapEntry.description: An entry in the Voice Endpoint Connection Mapping table.

voiceEndptMapSlot.name: voiceEndptMapSlot
voiceEndptMapSlot.description: This MIB object contains the slot number associated with the requested connection endpoint.

voiceEndptMapChannel.name: voiceEndptMapChannel
voiceEndptMapChannel.description: This MIB object contains the channel number associated with the requested connection endpoint.

voiceEndptMapEndptPtr.name: voiceEndptMapEndptPtr
voiceEndptMapEndptPtr.description: This MIB object contains a pointer to first column of row in the service specific EndptTable which corresponds to the slot and channel specified in the columns above.

voiceEndptMapConnPtr.name: voiceEndptMapConnPtr
voiceEndptMapConnPtr.description: This MIB object contains a pointer to first column of row in connTable which corresponds to the slot and channel specified in the columns above.

shelfCnfgStatMaster.name: shelfCnfgStatMaster
shelfCnfgStatMaster.description: This object provides the network manager the IP address of the master statistics collection management workstation.

shelfCnfgStatCollIntvl.name: shelfCnfgStatCollIntvl
shelfCnfgStatCollIntvl.description: This object provides the network manager the current TFTP statistics collection file interval configured on the switch in minutes.

shelfCnfgStatBcktIntvl.name: shelfCnfgStatBcktIntvl
shelfCnfgStatBcktIntvl.description: This object provides the network manager the current TFTP statistics collection bucket interval configured on the switch in minutes.

shelfCnfgStatTimeSync.name: shelfCnfgStatTimeSync
shelfCnfgStatTimeSync.description: This object provides the network manager the current time for TFTP statistics collection. This object replaces the functionality originally supplied by the daytime handler application.

shelfCnfgSwError.name: shelfCnfgSwError
shelfCnfgSwError.description: This object notifies the network manager that a switch software error has has been logged on this shelf.

shelfCnfgCardError.name: shelfCnfgCardError
shelfCnfgCardError.description: This object notifies the network manager that a switch card error has has been logged on this shelf.

nodeGrpAlarmState.name: nodeGrpAlarmState
nodeGrpAlarmState.description: Node Alarm State. Only low 6 bits are valid.

nodeGrpGateway.name: nodeGrpGateway
nodeGrpGateway.description: Is this node acting as a gateway?

nodeRstTimeout.name: nodeRstTimeout
nodeRstTimeout.description: Timeout for resetting PVC rate to QIR.

alarmTrapSequenceNumber.name: alarmTrapSequenceNumber
alarmTrapSequenceNumber.description: The Sequence Number of the last trap generated on the SNMP Proxy

trunkEntry.name: trunkEntry
trunkEntry.description: An entry in the Trunk table.

trunkLocalSlot.name: trunkLocalSlot
trunkLocalSlot.description: Local Slot Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

trunkLocalPort.name: trunkLocalPort
trunkLocalPort.description: Local Port Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

trunkLocalLine.name: trunkLocalLine
trunkLocalLine.description: Local Line Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

trunkCardType.name: trunkCardType
trunkCardType.description: Type of the card supporting the trunk line. The card type is dependant on the value of nodePlatform. Additional types may exist with future hardware.

trunkInterface.name: trunkInterface
trunkInterface.description: Trunk Line Interface Type. Indicates the format of the packet line.

trunkLineLoad.name: trunkLineLoad
trunkLineLoad.description: Line Load in packets per second.

trunkComment.name: trunkComment
trunkComment.description: StrataView user entered comment field used to further qualify the trunk line.

trunkBurstyDataBQDepth.name: trunkBurstyDataBQDepth
trunkBurstyDataBQDepth.description: Trunk Line bursty data B queue depth.

trunkBurstyDataBQEfcnThreshold.name: trunkBurstyDataBQEfcnThreshold
trunkBurstyDataBQEfcnThreshold.description: Trunk Line bursty data B queue EFCN/FFCI threshold.

trunkClpHighDropThreshold.name: trunkClpHighDropThreshold
trunkClpHighDropThreshold.description: Trunk Line CLP high dropping threshold.

trunkClpLowDropThreshold.name: trunkClpLowDropThreshold
trunkClpLowDropThreshold.description: Trunk Line CLP low dropping threshold.

cirLineEntry.name: cirLineEntry
cirLineEntry.description: An entry in the Circuit Line table.

cirLineInterface.name: cirLineInterface
cirLineInterface.description: Circuit Line Interface Type. Indicates the format of the circuit line.

cirLineComment.name: cirLineComment
cirLineComment.description: Comment entered by StrataView user to further qualify the Circuit Line.

cirLinePortNumber.name: cirLinePortNumber
cirLinePortNumber.description: Always returned as 0 for GET requests. ASI port number is filled-in for TRAPs.

frpTable.name: frpTable
frpTable.description: The table of Frame Relay Ports.

frpEntry.name: frpEntry
frpEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Ports table.

frpLocalPort.name: frpLocalPort
frpLocalPort.description: Local Port Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

frpPortSpeed.name: frpPortSpeed
frpPortSpeed.description: Port Speed in bits per second.

frpComment.name: frpComment
frpComment.description: StrataView User comment used to further qualify the Frame Relay Port.

frpEcnThreshold.name: frpEcnThreshold
frpEcnThreshold.description: Frame Relay Port ECN queue threshold.

connEntry.name: connEntry
connEntry.description: An entry in the Connections table.

connLocalChannel.name: connLocalChannel
connLocalChannel.description: Local Channel Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

connRemoteChannel.name: connRemoteChannel
connRemoteChannel.description: Remote Channel Number. These are numbered starting at 1.

connRate.name: connRate
connRate.description: Combination Field of Rate Info. The value for this variable is generated by ORing together the following: 0x80 -> Fast Eia Enabled 0x40 -> DFM Enabled 0x08 -> 7/8 Encoding 0x10 -> 8/8 Encoding 0x18 -> 8/8 Inverted Encoding 0x20 -> 7/8 Inverted Encoding 0x01 -> Voice 0x02 -> Non-Time Stamped 0x03 -> Time Stamped 0x04 -> bursty data 0x05 -> multicast These form four fields: bit 7, bit 6, bits 3-5, and bits 0-2.

connLocalMaxPkts.name: connLocalMaxPkts
connLocalMaxPkts.description: Local maximum number of packets per second allocated.

connRemoteMaxPkts.name: connRemoteMaxPkts
connRemoteMaxPkts.description: Remote maximum number of packets per second allocated.

connMinBandwidth.name: connMinBandwidth
connMinBandwidth.description: Minimum guaranteed bandwidth in bits per second. Zero if not meaningful.

connTXR.name: connTXR
connTXR.description: Flag to identify voice connection end point card is TXR card type.

connComment.name: connComment
connComment.description: StrataView user entered comment field used to further qualify the connection.

connCMax.name: connCMax
connCMax.description: Connection maximum threshold for FRP credit manager.

connConnInfoFlag.name: connConnInfoFlag
connConnInfoFlag.description: Connection information flags. The flags are define as: bit 6 snaPriorityHigh - decimal 64 bit 7 forsightEnabled - decimal 128 A value of 0 indicates no bits are set.

connABitStatus.name: connABitStatus
connABitStatus.description: Connection Bit status field. The fields defined are: bit 6 remotePacketLine - decimal 64 bit 7 aBitOk - decimal 128. A value of 0 indicates no bits are set.

connLocalLine.name: connLocalLine
connLocalLine.description: Local Line Number. Valid only for AXIS

cirLineRTCTable.name: cirLineRTCTable
cirLineRTCTable.description: The table of Circuit Line statistics.

cirLineRTCEntry.name: cirLineRTCEntry
cirLineRTCEntry.description: An entry in the Circuit Line statistics table. Each row may be sparse.

cirLineRTCBipolarViolations.name: cirLineRTCBipolarViolations
cirLineRTCBipolarViolations.description: The number of bipolar violations which have occurred on the line. This statistic is valid for T1 circuits only.

cirLineRTCFrameSlips.name: cirLineRTCFrameSlips
cirLineRTCFrameSlips.description: The number of frame slips which have occurred on the receive side of the line. This statistic is valid for TXR lines only. CIP and CDP cards do not support this statistic.

cirLineRTCOutOfFrames.name: cirLineRTCOutOfFrames
cirLineRTCOutOfFrames.description: The number of 0 -> 1 transitions of the out of frame conditions as detected by the hardware.

cirLineRTCLossesOfSignal.name: cirLineRTCLossesOfSignal
cirLineRTCLossesOfSignal.description: The number of 0 -> 1 transitions of the loss of signal condition as detected by the hardware. This statistic is valid on CIP and CDP lines only. TXR lines do not support this statistic.

cirLineRTCFrameBitErrors.name: cirLineRTCFrameBitErrors
cirLineRTCFrameBitErrors.description: The number of frame alignment signal errors which are detected on a line. This statistic is valid only on lines supported by CIP and CDP cards. TXR cards do not support this statistic.

cirLineRTCCrcErrors.name: cirLineRTCCrcErrors
cirLineRTCCrcErrors.description: The number of CRC errors detected on the line. This statistic is valid on lines supported by CIP and CDP cards. TXR cards do no support this statistic.

cirLineRTCOutOfMultiFrames.name: cirLineRTCOutOfMultiFrames
cirLineRTCOutOfMultiFrames.description: The number of 0 -> 1 transitions into out of multi-frame as detected by the hardware. This statistic is valid only on E1 lines. T1 lines do not support this statistic.

This statistic is valid for Frame Relay Connections only.

connRTCXmitFrames.name: connRTCXmitFrames
connRTCXmitFrames.description: The number of frames transmitted out the FRP port which were received from the other endpoint of the connection. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

connRTCXmitFramesDiscarded.name: connRTCXmitFramesDiscarded
connRTCXmitFramesDiscarded.description: The number of frames to be transmitted out the FRP port which were received from the other endpoint of the connection, but were discarded due to the age of the frame in the IPX system, a CRC error, or lack of buffer space. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay Connections only.

connRTCRcvdPkts.name: connRTCRcvdPkts
connRTCRcvdPkts.description: The number of packets received from the Muxbus by the FRP port associated with the connection endpoint. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay Connections only.

connRTCRcvdPktsDiscarded.name: connRTCRcvdPktsDiscarded
connRTCRcvdPktsDiscarded.description: The number of packets received from the Muxbus at the FRP port associated with the connection endpoint, but were discarded before being ssembled into frames and transmitted on the FRP port. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay Connections only.

connRTCXmitPkts.name: connRTCXmitPkts
connRTCXmitPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted from one connection endpoint onto the Muxbus towards the other connection endpoint. This statistic is valid for all types of inter-node connections, and for CDP Data, FRP, LDP and SDP terminated DAX connections.

connRTCXmitPktsProjected.name: connRTCXmitPktsProjected
connRTCXmitPktsProjected.description: The estimated number of packets which would be used if DSI or DFM were enabled for the connection. This statistic is valid for inter-node voice connections and with all types of data connections. It is not valid for DAX voice connections or Frame Relay connections.

connRTCXmitPktsSupervisory.name: connRTCXmitPktsSupervisory
connRTCXmitPktsSupervisory.description: The number of supervisory packets transmitted from one connection endpoint to another. Supervisory packets reflect signaling bit transitions for voice connections, and EIA lead transitions for data channels. This statistic is valid on all inter-node 'a', 'c', and 'v' voice connections, all inter-node data connections, all 'd' type voice connection endpoints which are supported by CIP or CDP cards, and all DAX data connections. This statistic is not valid for Frame Relay connections.

connRTCRcvdBytes.name: connRTCRcvdBytes
connRTCRcvdBytes.description: The number of frame bytes received from the FRP port associated with the connection endpoint. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

connRTCRcvdBytesDiscarded.name: connRTCRcvdBytesDiscarded
connRTCRcvdBytesDiscarded.description: The number of frame bytes received from the FRP port associated with the connection endpoint, but were discarded due to the age of the frame in the IPX system or the lack of buffer space before being transmitted onto the Muxbus. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

connRTCXmitBytes.name: connRTCXmitBytes
connRTCXmitBytes.description: The number of frame bytes to be received from the Muxbus from the remote end of the connection, which were actually transmitted out the FRP port as frames. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

connRTCXmitBytesDiscarded.name: connRTCXmitBytesDiscarded
connRTCXmitBytesDiscarded.description: The number of frame bytes to be received from the Muxbus from the remote end of the connection, but were discarded due to the age of the frame in the IPX system, a CRC error, or lack of buffer space. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

connRTCSecondsV25ModemOn.name: connRTCSecondsV25ModemOn
connRTCSecondsV25ModemOn.description: The number of seconds the V.25 modem has been detected and a connection upgraded from ADPCM to PCM. The status of the V.25 modem detect is checked every 3 seconds, so the granularity of the data which makes up this statistic is 3 seconds. This statistic is valid for inter- node type 'a', 'c' and 'v' voice connections only.

connRTCSecondsDsiEnabled.name: connRTCSecondsDsiEnabled
connRTCSecondsDsiEnabled.description: The number of seconds that a connection has been performing Digital Speech Interpolation (DSI). The status of DSI is checked every 3 seconds, so the granularity of the data which makes up this statistic is 3 seconds. This statistic is valid for inter-node type 'c' and 'v' voice connections only.

connRTCSecondsOffHook.name: connRTCSecondsOffHook
connRTCSecondsOffHook.description: The number of seconds that a voice connection has been off-hook. The on-hook state is determined by the signaling bits, as defined by the 'cnfchtp' command. A connection which is not on-hook is treated as off-hook for this statistic. The status of the off-hook condition is checked every 3 seconds, so the granularity of the data which makes up this statistic is 3 seconds. This statistic is valid for all 'a', 'c' and 'v' voice connections, and for 'd' type voice connection endpoints supported by CIP or CDP cards.

connRTCSecondsInService.name: connRTCSecondsInService
connRTCSecondsInService.description: The number of seconds that a connection has been in service. A conection is considered to be in service if its end points are not in alarm, that cards required to support the connection are present, and the connection is routed.

connRTCXmitFramesWithFECN.name: connRTCXmitFramesWithFECN

connRTCXmitFramesWithBECN.name: connRTCXmitFramesWithBECN
connRTCXmitFramesWithBECN.description: The number of frames transmitted out the FRP port with the BECN bit set. This statistic is valid for Frame Relay connections only.

databaseSampleFreq.name: databaseSampleFreq
databaseSampleFreq.description: The desired rate (in seconds) at which the database should be queried for new log records that match any of the filter criteria from the Event Filter Table. The agent may optionally poll more or less frequently then specified by this variable. The value of this variable is only a suggestion to the agent.

currentMaxLogIndex.name: currentMaxLogIndex
currentMaxLogIndex.description: The current max value of logIndex. This value may change with time.

maintLogEntry.name: maintLogEntry
maintLogEntry.description: An entry in the log table.

logIndex.name: logIndex
logIndex.description: Unique index of the Log record.

logNetwork.name: logNetwork
logNetwork.description: Name of the network for which this log entry was generated.

logNodeName.name: logNodeName
logNodeName.description: Name of the IPX node for this this log entry was generated.

logGmtDate.name: logGmtDate
logGmtDate.description: ASCII formatted string indicating the GMT date and time for this log record in the format (yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss). This is the time reported by the IPX which generated the event.

logSeverity.name: logSeverity
logSeverity.description: The severity of this log record.

logMsg.name: logMsg
logMsg.description: An ASCII message associated with this log record.

eventFilterEntry.name: eventFilterEntry
eventFilterEntry.description: An entry in the Event Filter table. Each entry in this table describes a set of log entry criteria, and entries in the log that match these criteria will be forwarded as SNMP TRAPS.

eventFilterIndex.name: eventFilterIndex
eventFilterIndex.description: The unique index for each entry of this table. This entry can only be written with the first SET command to create a new row of this table.

eventFilterStatus.name: eventFilterStatus
eventFilterStatus.description: 'active' indicates that this row of the table is currently generating filtered TRAPs. When in this state, any entry added to the log table with logSeverity matching eventFilterSeverity and logMsg containing the eventFilterSubstring text, this information will be forwarded as a TRAP. 'invalid' indicates that this row of the table is no longer generating filtered TRAPs. A conforming agent may either leave the row with the 'invalid' value in the table, or may delete the row from the table.

eventFilterSeverity.name: eventFilterSeverity
eventFilterSeverity.description: The eventFilterSeverity specifies the severity of log records to be forwarded on as SNMP TRAPS by this event filter entry. The value of eventFilterSeverty must exactly match the value of logSeverity for there to be a chance that a new log record will be forwarded as a TRAP. An eventFilterSeverity of length 0 matches all severity levels.

eventFilterSubstring.name: eventFilterSubstring
eventFilterSubstring.description: The eventFilterSubstring variable specifies an ASCII substring that must appear in the logMsg field of a log record in order for there to be a chance that for the log record to forwarded as a TRAP. If this variable contains a zero length string, the substring comparison will always SUCCEED for this event filter entry.

maintLogFilterTimeMin.name: maintLogFilterTimeMin
maintLogFilterTimeMin.description: When maintLogFilterTimeMin has a value other than a 0 length string, the value is used as a minimum value for maintLogFilterGmtDate to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. The string is formated as yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss

maintLogFilterTimeMax.name: maintLogFilterTimeMax
maintLogFilterTimeMax.description: When maintLogFilterTimeMax has a value other than a 0 length string, the value is used as a maximum value for maintLogFilterGmtDate to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. The string is formated as yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss

maintLogFilterWindow.name: maintLogFilterWindow
maintLogFilterWindow.description: When maintLogFilterWindow has a value other than 0, the value is used to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. This attribute has the effect of limiting the view in the maintLogTable to the number specified by the value of this attribute. If after applying the other maintLogFilter attributes, the remaining set exceeds the value of maintLogFilterWindow then, the set of entries which can be viewed is limited to the top N based on the logIndex value.

maintLogFilterNetworkName.name: maintLogFilterNetworkName
maintLogFilterNetworkName.description: When maintLogFilterNetworkName has a value other than a 0 length string, then the value of this attribute is used to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. This value must match logNetwork exactly to pass the filter.

maintLogFilterNodeName.name: maintLogFilterNodeName
maintLogFilterNodeName.description: When maintLogFilterNodeName has a value other than a 0 length string, then the value of this attribute is used to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. This value must match logNodeName exactly to pass the filter.

maintLogFilterSeverity.name: maintLogFilterSeverity
maintLogFilterSeverity.description: When maintLogFilterSeverity has a value other than a 0 length string, then the value is used to qualify entries in the maintLogTable. The value must match the logSeverity exactly to pass the filter.
